: 1725954057:0;gh repo edit --description "This repository automates the deployment of a Hugo static site to AWS S3 using OIDC authentication and a custom IAM role. The project includes GitHub Actions workflows for building the Hugo site and pushing files to S3, while integrating Route 53 and CloudFront for DNS and CDN management. Future plans include converting the setup into a public Terraform module."
: 1725954129:0;gh repo edit --description "This project uses OIDC to authenticate with AWS services (S3, Route 53, CloudFront) via a custom IAM role. It features GitHub Actions to build and deploy a Hugo site to an S3 bucket. Future plans include converting it into a Terraform module for easy reuse and multi-environment support."
